{{Infobox artwork | title = Last Supper | image = Last supper - Vasco Fernandes.jpg | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | painting_alignment = | other_language_1 = Portuguese | other_title_1 = Última Ceia ou Instituição da Sagrada Eucaristia | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = Grão Vasco | year = 1535 | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | catalogue = | material = oil on canvas | subject = | height_metric = 151 <!-- (i.e. in metric units) --> | width_metric = 201.5 | length_metric = | height_imperial = <!-- (i.e. in imperial units) --> | width_imperial = | length_imperial = | diameter_metric = | diameter_imperial = | metric_unit = cm <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | imperial_unit = in <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | dimensions = | dimensions_ref = | condition = | owner = | accession = | museum = Grão Vasco Museum | city = Viseu | coordinates = <!-- Only use for the coordinates (when known) of the artwork itself, i.e. not for the site, building, structure, etc where it is kept, otherwise leave blank (or omit): {{coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | preceded_by = <!-- preceding work by the same artist --> | followed_by = <!-- next work by the same artist --> | website = <!-- Official webpage/site only: {{URL|example.com}} --> }} The '''''Last Supper''''' (Portuguese: '''''Última Ceia ou Instituição da Sagrada Eucaristia''''') is an altarpiece by [[Grão Vasco]] Fernandes, from 1535.
== Description == The painting is an oil on canvas with overall dimensions of 151 x 201.5 centimeters. It is in the collection of the [[Grão Vasco Museum]], in [[Viseu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.matriznet.dgpc.pt/MatrizNet/Objectos/ObjectosConsultar.aspx?IdReg=207672|title=MatrizNet|publisher=|accessdate=16 May 2016}}</ref>
== Analysis == The triptych from the [[chapel of Santa Marta]], of the ancient Archbishop's Palace at [[Viseu|Fontelo]],<ref>[http://www.monumentos.pt/Site/APP_PagesUser/SIPA.aspx?id=7285 Building reconstructed and now is the Dão Wine Manor house]</ref><ref>[https://www.google.pt/maps/place/Solar+Do+Vinho+Do+D%C3%A3o/@40.6601378,-7.9103587,15.96z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0xd233644435baff1:0x2254607db29b1d0e!8m2!3d40.6612813!4d-7.9010475 Localization by GoogleMaps]</ref> shows the [[Last Supper]], with [[Judas]] leaving on the left panel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.europeana.eu/portal/record/2063606/POR_280_008.html|title=The Last Supper - Grão Vasco|website=www.europeana.eu}}</ref>
